The paper deals with sublinear time algorithms for counting subgraphs in a graph and estimating the selectivity of self-join queries in database systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of graph theory and the study of the degree sequence of a graph also suggest that the paper could belong to categories related to graph theory (cs.CG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
